This paper deals with consensus dynamics for multi-agent systems, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of systems and control (cs.SY), multi-agent systems (cs.MA), and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of observability theory, which is relevant to signal processing (cs.SI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
